<div id="section5">
<div class="background-contaioner">
    <h1 class="main-heading">Consitency</h1>
    <div class="card-para">
    <p class="about-content">
        Database must be in consistent state before and after the execution of the transaction. This ensures that there are no errors in the database at any point of time. Application programmer is responsible for maintaining the consistency of the database.
    </p>
    <p class="bold-content">Example:</p>
    <p class="about-content">A transferring 1000 dollars to B. A’s initial balance is 2000 and B’s initial balance is 5000.</p>
    <p class="bold-content">Before the transaction:</p>
    <p class="about-content">Total of A+B = 2000 + 5000 = 7000$</p>
    <p class="bold-content">After the transaction:</p>
    <p class="about-content">Total of A+B = 1000 + 6000 = 7000$</p>
    <p class="bold-content">The data is consitendct before and after the execution of the transaction so this example maintains the consistency property of the database.</p>
</div>
